HEADWORD: Anadromous
<hw>A*nad"ro*mous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
running upward; <?/ + <?/ a running, <?/ to run.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Ascending rivers from the sea, at certain
seasons, for breeding, as the salmon, shad, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Tending upwards; -- said of terns
in which the lowest secondary segments are on the upper side of the
branch of the central stem.</def> <rj><au>D. C. Eaton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

